Install Flask: Use pip install Flask to install the Flask framework if not already installed.

Create a Python File: Save the Flask code in a file, e.g., app.py.

Open Terminal/Command Prompt: Navigate to the directory where the app.py file is located.

Run the Application: Execute the command python app.py to start the Flask server.

Access the Application: Open a web browser and go to http://localhost:5000/ to interact with the application.
